# 1. Introduction

Sliding Window is one of the most important techniques in DSA.

It is used to:

- Optimize nested loops
- Reduce time complexity
- Process subarrays/substrings efficiently
- Solve many interview questions

Many O(n²) problems can become O(n).

---

# 2. What is Sliding Window?

A Sliding Window is a range of consecutive elements that moves through an array or string.

Instead of recalculating everything for every subarray:

- Remove left element
- Add right element
- Update answer

Window slides one step at a time.

---

## Visualization

Array:

```text
[2, 1, 5, 1, 3, 2]
```

Window Size = 3

```text
[2 1 5] 1 3 2

2 [1 5 1] 3 2

2 1 [5 1 3] 2

2 1 5 [1 3 2]
```

Window keeps sliding.

---

# 3. Why Sliding Window?

Without Sliding Window:

```java
for every subarray
    calculate answer again
```

Time Complexity:

```text
O(n²)
```

With Sliding Window:

```java
remove old
add new
```

Time Complexity:

```text
O(n)
```

Huge improvement.

