# 5. Types of Sliding Window

There are mainly two types:

---

## Type 1

Fixed Size Window

```text
Window Size = K
```

Examples:

- Maximum sum of size K
- Average of size K
- First negative number in every window

---

## Type 2

Variable Size Window

Window grows and shrinks.

Examples:

- Longest substring without repeating characters
- Smallest subarray with sum ≥ K
- Longest subarray with K distinct elements

---

# 6. Fixed Size Sliding Window

---

## Brute Force

Find max sum of size K.

```java
for(i=0;i<=n-k;i++)
{
    sum = 0;

    for(j=i;j<i+k;j++)
        sum += arr[j];
}
```

Complexity:

```text
O(n*k)
```

---

## Optimized Sliding Window

### Idea

First Window:

```text
Calculate once
```

Then:

```text
Remove left element
Add new right element
```

---

### Example

Array:

```text
[2,1,5,1,3,2]
```

K = 3

First Window:

```text
2+1+5 = 8
```

Next:

```text
8 - 2 + 1 = 7
```

Next:

```text
7 - 1 + 3 = 9
```

Next:

```text
9 - 5 + 2 = 6
```

Maximum:

```text
9
```

---

## Fixed Window Template

```java
int windowSum = 0;

for(int i=0;i<k;i++)
{
    windowSum += arr[i];
}

int max = windowSum;

for(int end=k;end<n;end++)
{
    windowSum += arr[end];
    windowSum -= arr[end-k];

    max = Math.max(max, windowSum);
}
```

---

# 7. Variable Size Sliding Window

Most interview questions belong here.

---

## Structure

```java
start = 0

for(end = 0 to n-1)
{
    expand window

    while(condition invalid)
    {
        shrink window
        start++
    }

    update answer
}
```

---

# 8. Core Idea

Window has two pointers:

```text
start
end
```

Window:

```text
[start ... end]
```

---

## Expand

```java
end++
```

Add element.

---

## Shrink

```java
start++
```

Remove element.

---

# 9. General Template

```java
int start = 0;

for(int end=0; end<n; end++)
{
    // include arr[end]

    while(window invalid)
    {
        // remove arr[start]
        start++;
    }

    ans = update();
}
```

