# 13. Time Complexity

---

## Fixed Window

Each element visited once.

```text
O(n)
```

---

## Variable Window

Both pointers move once.

```text
O(n)
```

---

## Why O(n)?

Because:

```text
start moves n times
end moves n times
```

Total:

```text
2n = O(n)
```

---

# 14. Common Mistakes

---

## Mistake 1

Using nested loops.

Think:

```text
Can I slide?
```

---

## Mistake 2

Forgetting to remove left element.

```java
sum -= arr[start];
```

---

## Mistake 3

Wrong window length

Correct:

```java
end-start+1
```

Not:

```java
end-start
```

---

## Mistake 4

Using Sliding Window on negative numbers blindly.

Example:

```text
[-2,5,-1]
```

May break logic.

Need Prefix Sum in many cases.

